Hi all!

This pack is a set of variants of the Blade Super Heavy Tank. In the pack you get all the parts to print the following:

- Deathblade
- Hellblade
- Shadowblade
- Quakeblade
- Thunderblade

This pack is designed to conform to 6mm scale games, but increase their scale by 33.3% for 8mm scaled games.

In addition, this series of tanks features modular armour and sponson mounts. You get a selection of parts to outfit the sponsons and turrets any way you deem fit, and there are included magnet holes for ease of installation (2x1mm) for the large secondary turrets.

You also get a hatch part that can be installed if you don't want a turret there (perhaps using underslung turrets only?)

Anyway, enjoy, thanks for reading :)

Tiny tanks! The perfect thing to give a sense of scale to your tiny titans, tiny aircraft, or tiny anything! Add them as base decoration, add them as terrain decoration, create tiny war dioramas, do whatever you want with them! Anything is made better with the addition of tiny tanks.

We've long since jumped the shark when it comes to tiny biggest tank designs. But just in case you're one of those tiny generals who is sure that more gunz is even better here's the overcompensation tank.

Tiny tanks are intended for resin printers.

You should print 1 chassis, 4 point defense turrets, and 2 main turrets (one mirrored) for each tank you want.

A heavily reworked version of the awesome TINY BIGGEST TANK MBT by Woddish with custom glacis and turrets crafted to visually resemble the design cues of the Tiny Bigger Tank MBT to bridge the two designs. The main turret is fully interchangeable with that tank (for additional modeling joy). The smaller turrets will fully work with my TINY BIGGEST TANK REDUX as well. This was inspired by the brilliant 40k kitbash as well as the classic 2nd Edition epic figure.

Blender source included!

Update 20221222: TheZomby has graciously provided not one but two new alternate main turrets for our use! Big ups!

Update 2023.04.03: Added an additional hatch on the upper deck of the chassis. The area looked a little empty of details in real life.

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

Originally produced by Games Workshop for their 6mm scale table top wargame, Epic 40,000 (and precessors/successors). They have since abandoned all support for Epic, so I modeled this in Autodesk Inventor for any avid wargamers.

I haven't tried printing this model in an FDM printer so I can't recommend settings or methods of optimization.

Using the awesome Macharius tank designed by Mkhand_Industries I put together this custom closed turret (Armageddon) Omega variant. This tank is scaled for Epic 40k however if you would like to print it for use in normal Warhammer 40k simply up scale it by 498.75%. The tank is currently one piece which is how I typically prefer to print on my Ender 3.


Macharius Omega Lore:

The Macharius Omega is a variant of the Macharius Heavy Tank used by the Imperial Guard. The Macharius Omega differs from the standard Macharius tank and its other variants due to its unique main weapon. The Macharius Omega is a war-machine built with a single purpose, the battlefield deployment of the Omega Pattern Plasma Blastgun.

This weapon is a variant of the common Ryza Pattern Plasma Blastgun commonly deployed on the Stormblade super-heavy tank. The Omega Pattern is smaller and lighter than the Ryza Pattern, as it uses a compact generator and smaller force crucible allowing it to be mounted on smaller armoured hulls, such as the Macharius. The downside of this version of the Plasma Blastgun is that it is less stable and generates considerably more heat than the Ryza Pattern, but fortunately it is also much easier to manufacture.
